  "title": "Twilight Bride",
  "secondName": "Twilight Bride",
  "description": "Come one, come all, to toast the dying year.\n\nAstrid has prepared a feast for all of winter's wanderers. Her hearth burns warm and her table seats hundreds. As soon as night falls, she opens her gates and welcomes monster and innocent alike. She has been both. She knows that life flies by, no matter who you are, no matter what you've done. It is what separates the mortals from the gods.\n\nFew view death as a celebration. But then, few can see it through Astrid's eyes.\n\nMortality, the chance to grow and change, is the greatest gift a soul can be given.",
